  "body": "#### System information\n\nGeth version: `geth 1.4.*`\nOS & Version: Ubuntu 14\n#### Expected behaviour\n\nReturn raw transaction along with transaction json data. After sending, transaction json representation stays the same.\n#### Actual behaviour\n\nIn versions 1.4.0-1.4.3 signTransaction returns json like \n{\n  raw: \"0xf8658085051251fec083015f9094095a9ae02a321cc7a90c298788055c5dc335ddf680801ca061e4d07f1d0c03efc1869ed70d9c1d568757e8a26d3f98412f53c543bfeda949a07f489f8990ebb57afa1fa6db034fd638d82c261722dde2c1d109b0569525431d\",\n  tx: {\n    data: ..,\n    **from: \"0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000000\",**\n    gas: ...,\n    gasPrice: ...,\n    hash: \"0xe938b511610b45149c0cf09dd598f45f7afecf67ed5abb936df920a5e838661f\",\n    nonce: ...,\n    to: ...\n    value: ..\n  }\n}\n\nWhen i send such transaction, it appears in pool with proper 'from' attribute and **different** hash. I know, that it is unofficial method, but it worked great in previous versions and I hope you will not just remove it or leave in such state.\n",
